28/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- A US congressional delegation led by Representative Bob Goodlatte met with Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis and Transport Minister Michalis Liapis on Friday (25 February).
After the talks, Goodlatte confirmed that Washington considers Athens an important ally in the region and attaches great significance to bilateral relations.
He also suggested that members of the US business community are eyeing investment opportunities in Greece, particularly in the telecommunications sector.
Also Friday, South African President Thabo Mbeki wrapped up a three-day visit to Athens.
Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis pledged increased peacekeeping efforts as well as greater EU aid to African countries.
Mbeki called on Greek companies to invest in his country.
(Kathimerini - 26/02/05;
ANA, MPA, SABC News - 25/02/05)
